caption: Great

I went there, customer service was good. The dumplings are fresh.I order a wonton soup and it was like boiling water..way to hot to consume.i had to wait approx 30 minutes for it to cool off.Besides the soup the dumplings are worth trying.
Very good fresh and nice people
Got pan-fried dumplings, shrimp, and soup dumplings.  Everything was bland. Soup dumplings had little soup and were too thick and doughy.  Better off going to Sunset Park
Probably the best dumplings I've ever had. Def recommend the special pancakes and rainbow dumplings. You can tell that their food is made with love.
Amazing soups and dumpling.

My 3.5 year old gets psyched whenever we order the rainbow dumplings from Kathy's. Yummy dumplings and quick delivery.  Pan fried pork dumplings are solid. The juicy pork buns warm your cold soul on a winter day. Big believer in the Special Pancakes.
Exceptional food, super nice employees, constantly good mood. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is good. 5 stars.

I ordered Kathy’s Special Pancakes and a Mango Boba Tea. I was very happy with both items. You could tell the food was freshly made and used fresh ingredients. The shrimp inside the pancakes looked and tasted new, and the pancakes themselves were very crispy. It came with four rolled pancakes and was a good snack that felt about the size of an appetizer. The boba was nice and chewy, while the flavor of the tea was refreshing. I’d definitely go back again if I’m in the area to try out other things on their menu.
Wow! The dumplings taste really good! The passion fruit bubble tea and mango smoothie was also really good. Very good service! I am definitely coming back. :)
Great food the sweet and sour soup was amazing and the dumplings were great this is my new go to place all there food tastes fresh and homemade!

Good food at a great price. What’s not to love?  All dumpling fans should visit this place as their selection far outweighs any average Chinese restaurant. This is their specialty and they do it very well. The staff is pleasant and the place always looks clean. It’s become one of my favorite spots for a quick bite.
Tasty but overpriced.
A little pricey but food is delicious and staff are friendly :) Thanks!
Food here is always delicious and tastes fresh. I've had most of their menu over the past few years -- no complaints.
I really like the dumplings here, haven't tried much else, they forgot something from my take out but I didn't get far before I realized it, and they ran it out to the car!
Their Indian pancake was so good. Their taro bubble tea was okay. Very clean establishment. Their bathroom was well kept. The service was lovely. I will definitely come back.
Nice people and good food
Ordered from Grubhub. Amazing food and service!
Dumplings are very good. Probably one of the best in Brooklyn. Thing is I had to wait at least 15-20 minutes for 2 small orders.
Dumplings arent as good as they use to be
Delicious dumplings.
Good for the nabe
Nice food was tasty small I believe they had a restroom quaint
Best pan fried pork dumplings I've ever had, this is true perfection! Try the almond bubble tea too, i go every week.

Quaint little dumpling spot. Staff was friendly, and selection is decent. I found the prices a little high, compared to some other places. The pan-fried pork dumplings were very good, but the soup dumplings left much to be desired. Skin was a bit think, insides weren't too hot and very little liquid. They also don't have larger soup dumplings spoons, making eating them difficult with a tiny plastic soon.
Best dumplings in Bay Ridge!

I’ve had their food over the last two years and thought it was great, however, recently that started to change. I went to pick up take away today and ordered ‘Indian pancake’ and hot-spicy soup. The pancake was DRIPPING IN OIL. By dripping I mean, literally. It was sitting in a pool of oil. I thought maybe it was the seasoning of the filling, but nope, the pancake was drenched it oil even and clearly non seasoned. I tried to use tissues to absorb the oil so I can eat, but gave up after 12tissues as it was still oozing oil. It went into the garbage. Next the soup, it was a completely different soup. A pork dumpling soup! Wow!!! How can they get it so wrong!?!! Never going there ever!
I had Eggrolls and Vegtable Dumplings.  Really good.  Good Green Tea drink also. Recommended.
Great Food!
I had the Loofah and Shrimp boiled dumplings. The squash and shrimp were fresh. Delicious. Also, the shop is clean and comfy. Definitely will go back here
Ordered from them once. Found a metal shard in my food. Never again.
We enjoyed the steamed veg dumplings but the fried chicken dumings with celery were not that great
Tasty! Had the veggie steamed dumplings, pan fried pork dumplings, and wonton soup. Overall decent dumplings for the price (all that + boba and regular tea for ~$20)

Shrimp rolls followed by noodles with beef has to be one of the best meals I've had for under $10.00. What a deal and it was fantastic (watch out flushing). Excellent place I always go to when in Bklyn. Wish I still lived there.
Awesome food and deliveries always on time
Fresh vegetables and tasty jasmine green tea. Spring rolls definitely are greasy from being deep fried, the simple ingredients are super yummy.
Decent dumplings. Friendly staff.
Went there once and I will not go back. No flavor at all. Insipid. Banal.
So so good! Highly recommend!
I love there store, when I lived in bayridge I always ordered from them, I recommend their beef noodle soup and Indian pancake!!
Very cute little place with really good food. I got the vegetable dumplings with the Beef Noodle soup and I have no complaints. You'll enjoy it
Nice place! Real friendly, good bubble tea, I recommend the coconut, and dumplings made to order.
Very nice little place. They have great hot and sour soup and very good dumplings
Very good establishment. The food and the service is great.
Nice place.
Good dumplings. Service was ok but not spectacular.
Yum!!!!
dumplings are good service quick
This place has gone downhill. Maybe changed management? So salty and greasy. Used to be so good. Can’t eat here anymore.
Great food - very tasty, but they are slow.
Use to be the BeST place for spring rolls. Now its inedible  gross and oily.
Clean spot, friendly service, price is ok, food taste great!
I liked the g8 combo and their prices are very affordable. I woukd definitely go there again
All their food is good! I've tried their delivery service and it is also very prompt. Great place for takeout.
The service time for food takes too long. waited 20 minutes for an order of pan fried dumplings. I'm not coming back again.
Delicious food and great, comfy interior.
Always excellent. Tasty and friendly.
Liked the purple dumplings.
Good food, impolite service
Quiet polite fast service relaxing atmosphere
Handmade dumplings with fresh ingredients!!
highly recommended the wonton soup. it's has bok choy and beef wonton and the broth isn't salty
They always mix vegetarian and chicken/pork dumplings! If you are a vegetarian, steer clear of their dumplings. You never know what will be served. Their almond tea is really good!
Great place for a quick bite. Reasonable prices.
Awesome dumplings
Friendly service. The noodles weren't very good. It was a bit salty for my taste.
Kathy's dumplings is truly an amazing spot in bay ridge. If you are looking for quality dumplings, this is the place to go.

Sweet and simple. Got their chiviest beef boiled dumplings, warming of the soul bean curd soup, the freshest cucumber salad and crispiest spring rolls. Washed it all down with a not too overly sweet passion fruit bubble tea. All at a decent price worth the taste in food. Great for a quick bite, that satisfies more than regular Chinese restaurants.

Authentic dumplings from scratch. You can literally take a peek in the kitchen and see the ladies make it. You get 8 pieces for about 5/6 dollars which is pretty good for NY prices. I would definitely eat here again.
I love the food
Awesome dumplings, incredible tea and the scallion and Indian pancakes were heavenly.
I just got the bubble tea and it was so weak and practically tasteless. What a waste of 4 bucks.. at least the guy at the counter was nice and the bubbles we're fresh..
(Translated by Google) excellent, fast and courteous  (Original) excellent, rapide et courtois
Good food that's a little different from the other Takeout restaurants in the area
Fried or boiled, both are delicious.
I love the dumpling soup so much. I also really love their pan fried pork dumplings. The only thing I wish was a little bit better are the soup dumplings.

Simple, clean, affordable and friendly.  This is my usual stop after my bay ridge buckram yoga class.  Ever since the triathlon store closed and it turned into this nice little oasis I have been going here and not once disappointed.  Worth the try!

A remarkable place to go for dumplings in all of Bay Ridge.   Kathy has proven that dumplings need not be a cheap and greasy food.  Here it's tasty, healthy, and good for you. Orders take time to prepare. One of the lesser known items on the menu, the pork/egg dumplings with the violet hue to it, thanks to the cabbage.  Special pancakes are nice as was their hot milk tea.

While Bay Ridge has always had a good number of quality restaurants this new place is high on my list. The dumplings come in many styles - in soup, fried and steamed. These made to order bundles of tastiness should be part of your regular diet.  Done in the long thin style - Kathy's has all sorts of flavors to please all types of appetites. They deliver and are available through Seamless so you can get them to your door in quick fashion.  Take my advise and you will be smiling!

This place is unbelievable. They have great soup dumplings, fried dumplings and other dishes too. The spring rolls and pork buns are can't miss as well. Plus the prices are low. This would fit in up in Sunset Park's Chinatown, that's how good it is. A real nice surprise.
I never was dumplings fan, but this place rocks!!! My absolute favorite is Chicken And Pork Dumplings w. Carrot Juice. They also accepting orders online at DinnerOut  (get 15% off, coupon:DEAL15)
